                                                                                                                                     Surya, Sandipan in fray for Cup
            A CORRESPONDENT            Surya Sekhar                           
	Calcutta: Seven Indians, including GM Surya Sekhar Ganguly are in the fray for the World Cup knock-out chess meet that gets is to be held in Khanty-Mansiysk, Russia from November 20-December 15.         
	The other Indian participants in the event, which has 23 players with an Elo of 2700, are GM Krishnan Sasikiran, GM Sandipan Chanda, GM Parimarjan Negi, GM Abhijeet Gupta, GM Abhijit Kunte and Sriram Jha.         
	Surya Sekhar meets Anton Fillipov of Uzbekistan in the first round while Sasikiran meets GM Elwin LAmi of the Netherlands. Another city boy, Sandipan meets Mikhael Kobalia of Russia in his opener.         
	Among the other Indians, Jha faces eighth seed Alexander Grischuk while Kunte has the toughest draw in Alexie Shirov, seeded 14th.         
	Negi will fight it out against Vadim Milov of Switzerland while Gupta, seeded since he had won the world junior last year, faces GM Nikita Vitiugov of Russia.         
	Surya Sekhar, who left the city on Tuesday along with Sandipan said: I have prepared hard for the championship, but the preparation has not been opponent specific. I have worked hard on my middle-game and endgame. In addition, I have done physical training with Kuntal Ray. Sandipan too, has assisted me in my preparation.         
	Sandipan, when asked about his prospects, said: The format is such that you have to give your best from round one.         
	The player who wins the first game will have a tremendous advantage as the opponent will have a trying time coming back in the second.                                                                                                                       
